Izzuddin Yahya (reigned: 13281338) was the Governor of the provincial Satgaon.[1] Izzuddin was appointed the governor under the Tughlaq Sultantate. Shamsuddin Ilyas Shah took service under Izzuddin. After his death in 1338, Ilyas Shah took control of Satagon and declared independence from Delhi.[2] 
